<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="40" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CKS1" type="to">Chiang</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d40fn1">Carried to Chungking by <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Hurley</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-13">October 13, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss></hi>: My special representative,
                            Brigadier General <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Patrick J.
                                Hurley</persName>, is going out on a special mission<note n="2" xml:id="d40fn2">According to <hi rend="italic">The <persName corresp="#p_SJW1">Stilwell</persName> Papers</hi>, p. 236,
                                the purpose of the mission was “to arrange the final details of the
                                Cairo conference”. See also Lohbeck, p. 203.</note> and I am hoping
                            very much that you can see him when he gets to China. With every best
                            wish to you and Madame <persName corresp="#p_CKS1">Chiang
                                Kai-shek</persName>,</p>
                        <p>Always sincerely,</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RFD1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>